name: sherwin Santiago
review_text: My first snow experience....

name: Tatyana Kleshch
review_text: Otlichnoe mesto dlya vstrechi s nastoyashchey zimoy. Sneg i vse razvlecheniya na snegu. Super!!! Vezd platnyy. Arenda oborudovaniya po raznym cenam. Est dorozhe est deshevle. Est tualety i stoliki dlya barbekyu.
review_translated_text: A great place to meet real winter. Snow and all the entertainment on the snow. Super!!! Entry is paid. Equipment rental at different prices. Some are more expensive, some are cheaper. There are toilets and barbecue tables.

name: John
review_text: Great place for beginners

name: Vinay Sharma
review_text: Mount Baw Baw is a fantastic destination for a snow day. What makes it stand out is that it's often less crowded than other resorts, which allows you to truly enjoy the experience. The slopes are perfect for beginners and intermediate skiers and snowboarders, offering a great environment to learn and have fun without feeling overwhelmed by crowds. The atmosphere is relaxed, and with a bit of luck, you can get some great snow and make the most of your time on the mountain. It's a great choice if you want to enjoy the snow without the usual hustle and bustle.

name: Siqin Tao
review_text: Great place for weekend escape, but, there is no healthy food options, only junk food available in the restaurant

name: Abhishek Deokar
review_text: Went on a weekday during school holidays and wasn't bad in terms of traffic/crowds. Got parking at the top car park, and skiing wait at lift was about 15 mins, which isn't bad. Good option for snow if living in southeast Melbourne.

name: Mad Max
review_text: We went there just after the school holidays. Not many people around

name: Stevo Turner
review_text: Thought paying $20 for the toboggan park was silly  but actually the timed sessions along with the moving carpet back up the hill made it totally worth the $20. Kids were very happy.

name: Krishna B
review_text: Nice place close to visit and absolutely loved

name: David H
review_text: Hugely over priced tickets, food, parking & room. Poorly maintained toboggan slope (singular) and very small, have to pay for every aspect of this free snow and no areas to even let the kids play that doesn't cost. Would highly suggest any other mountain such as mount bulla which is paradise compared to here.

name: Dave Boyle
review_text: Snow was fine, resort was very disorganised. Website is a nightmare. Had to change the date of my booking, was an absolute headache, no one could help, no one could tell me if I was right to come on another date even though the website showed availability. The information about the package we purchased was conflicting and confusing. We went in the middle of winter and the cafe at the resort village was closed. When staff were asked about this they said that it was just open some days and other days it wasn't...??? Very helpful. The walk back up from the toboggan area is a nightmare for families with little children. Very steep, long and a bit slippery as well. Calamari and the chips in the restaurant were very nice. The "alpine burger" was awful.

name: Sunan Janya
review_text: snukdiikhaaetesiiydaayaipt`nthiiekhaaepidaihelnaekhbaang`yaangaetko`ekhaelwhlangcchaakklabmaakpwy555
review_translated_text: It was fun, but unfortunately, I only went when they opened some games, but it was okay. After I came back, I got sick. Haha.

name: Qianying Wang
review_text: Good place for tobogganing. Whatever kids or adults. We all love toboggan. Not sure about ski. Will try next time. Very close to city. 2.5 hrs.  Less people on weekdays.

name: Ayesha Khan
review_text:
We experienced the snowfall at Mt. Baw baw.
There are heaps of snow play activities for all ages. They had belts for kids/adults who were toboganning to bring them back after the slide which is great to avoid exhaustion and frustration in young ones who want non stop fun. The hire rates are also cheap.
Plenty of snow play areas, warm seating areas, Clean rest rooms and cafes.
We went through Icy creek. The drive was beautiful at Tourist rd, however due to weather conditions we experienced fallen trees on the rd. Drivers should be very careful and alert at all times.

name: Don Joseph
review_text:
It is such a shame that i went to Mount baw baw for the 3rd time for skiing with my begginer friends last week. The Hut run lift was the only one which was open and the T bar was closed and the reason which they told me was there is not much snow is those areas, which we believed as well

Our plan was to ski there for Wed, thu and friday. But the only Lift they were running was the Hut run.By thursday, the hut run trails were started to become ice and we decided to wait till friday morning to see if they are going to open the summit T bar which they did not. So all 13 of us decided to not ski there anymore and we went to Mount Hotham.

We still belived them that they did not open the summit T bar because of low snow in those area. But when i checked yesterday, i found that they closed the Hut run and opened the summit T bar despite they did not even get 1cm of Snow.  So what i can see from this is , they lied to us about the snow level and wanted to keep the Summit T bar trails from not getting used while the Hut run was ok to use.

This is very rude. We all 13 of us took time off from our work, spend around  $2000 each person for our 1 week trip to come to your village, stay in the villlage apartments, spend our money in Mount baw baw not to just use one lift  because u wanted to save the other trails for future customers. This is so disrespectful to our time and money.

I will not ever recommend Mount Baw Baw to any of my friends ever again.

My recomnmendation is to go to Mount Hotham. Yes i understand it will cost extra money. But if u r willing to spend around $2000 for a whole week trip, why not spend the extra 200 - 300 dollars and have a much better skiing place, much more lifts running all the time and the snow quality is 10 times better than Mount Baw Baw.

Shame on you Mount Baw Baw for lying to us.

name: Francis Krueger
review_text: Almost every area are closed

name: Clint
review_text: Little guy with a mow on ski lift was rude and had no experience dealing with new timers. Was boring and would not go again

name: Vlad
review_text: The place is just okay--nothing special. There's only one cafe to eat from, so expect limited food options and long waits during busy times. Also, the walkalator for the toboggan keeps stopping, which gets frustrating, especially with kids. Overall, it's a decent day trip if you're nearby.

name: Shang
review_text: Good baw baw

name: Kristal Caroz
review_text:
Our experience was poor.
We spent over $200 to be able to get to the mountains. At the time, there was no advisory of snow.
We were told the snow playground will close at 5:00pm
We arrived at 4:00pm, and then were told that they close at 4:30pm.
We were deprived from renting the tabogan and the staff said " I will not let you rent it anymore as we close soon"
I pleaded for the gentleman for at atleast one slide for the children as we drove 3 hours from Melbourne, and that we would not have come if they close at 4:30pm. that we were told otherwise.
I was told "We understand how long it takes for you to get here but I just cannot let you in anymore".
We should have been told before we entered the gate, before they took the money from us. im gutted. never again.

name: Nilupa Nayomi
review_text:
Mount Baw Baw - Disappointing and Unsafe Toboggan Experience

We recently visited Mount Baw Baw with high expectations for a fun family day in the snow, but our experience with the toboggan area was extremely disappointing and raised several safety concerns.

Firstly, the toboggan area is simply not safe for tobogganing. The entire section is very slippery, including the top starting area. There's no leveled surface to properly prepare before you start the ride, which makes it too easy to slip and fall even before getting on the toboggan.

Once you're on the sliding path, things don't get any better. The toboggan run is full of big holes and bumps, which makes the ride not only uncomfortable but genuinely dangerous. With so many people using the slope at once, there's a serious risk that someone could come down too fast and crash into those in front, causing injuries. We saw this nearly happen multiple times and it was honestly stressful.

Unfortunately, the management of the crowd and facilities left a lot to be desired. When it gets busy (which it usually is during the season), the whole place feels chaotic and poorly managed. There isn't enough staff supervising, and the safety rules don't seem to be enforced at all.

One of the serious downsides is that there's only one ambulance onsite for the whole mountain, which isn't comforting given how many people are there and the level of risk on the toboggan run.

It's also frustrating considering how much it costs--$67 just for entry, plus $20 extra for every person over age 4 to use the toboggan area. With these high prices, you'd expect much better safety measures and organisation from the management.

I do want to mention that the emergency response team on site were clearly trying their best with the resources they had, but they seemed overstretched due to the lack of support and planning.

Overall, I definitely can't recommend the toboggan area at Mount Baw Baw, especially for families with young kids. If safety and good management are your priorities (as they should be!), you're better off looking elsewhere until they make some much-needed improvements.

name: Joshy Pama
review_text: Beeeeautiful spot! Bit pricey, and absolutely chockers on weekends but that's expected. Staff were bloody ripper and very helpful

name: Tillie Tempest
review_text:
The most disappointing attempt at visiting the snow. We organised to go with our 2 year old to take her to the snow for the first time and instead of happy memories, we left with frustration and a very upset toddler. We arrived at 10am and were instructed by a staff member at the gate that all the parking had run out if we hadn't pre-purchased. We were instructed we could park along the main road and take a shuttle bus to enter the resort. Not ideal but accepted that was the outcome of not realising we needed to book ahead of time. We then parked around 200m down the road as by then a large number of cars were also needing to do the same. We started lining up and another staff member was working her way down the line for people to pay their entrance fee. She informed us it was $67 for the car load plus $10 per person for the shuttle bus. A total of $87 for me, my husband and our toddler. While I think this was still a bit steep for entry, I can justify the price IF that actually included parking INSIDE the resort. But no, this was charged for parking along the main road alongside entry which we still had to wait for a shuttle bus for.

We copped the cost and thought it is what it is but thought it was an absolute rort. We ended up lining up for over 45 minutes and in that time 2 buses collected people. These buses could only fit 10 people at a time so in the 45 minutes we were waiting for, we still had at least 25-30 people ahead of us. And each return trip for the buses seemed to take a minimum of 25 minutes.

In the end, with a toddler who had absolutely had enough and 2 very disappointed adults, we asked for a refund which was accepted (thankfully) and decided to leave and visit a different snow field a different day.

We visited Mt Baw Baw 8 years ago and had a pleasant experience then but after today, I can safely say we will not be attempting to visit anytime soon as the shuttle bus system and exorbitant entrance fees when the car ISN'T EVEN PARKED INSIDE THE RESORT left us extremely disappointed and frustrated at the way Mt Baw Baw manages its guests.

I understand it is a weekend in snow season but management need to have a good look a their systems as this was a terrible experience.

name: Hongru Ouyang (Owen)
review_text:
We drove to there on Saturday but was told to leave due to the extremely long queue of cars and the people prepaid already inside when we were in the queue, didn't impact our mood actually. Drove up again on Sunday morning with prepaid everything, lucky not a crazy busy time and only 10mins we were in. Getting rented equipments gave us a bit of headaches due to the queue again, but all in suggested time anyway.
Lucky the snow was great, nice instructors, easy access to everything. Good place for beginners, kids took the 2hr lesson and directly flew themselves, very impressive. We love this place.
I know some people had bad experiences or made low grade comments here, but as long as you understand the chain is compulsory and forced, and the natural snow is controlled by weather, you should bring everything you need with a heart full of longing to enjoy your trip, at least the staff we met and saw there were very friendly and responsible, just a couple of restaurant employees we experienced were a bit of...
Enjoy the Baw Baw.

name: Mike Moulton
review_text:
14th July 25 price is now $67 for cars. Roads are still not great. No improvements in 2 years.

2 years ago It's worth going for a look if you have never been before. $60 entrance fee, I think Vic Roads could fix one of the roads to Mt Baw Baw from Traralgon. Earlier you go the better to avoid traffic as I did.

You can get snow chains fitted for near 40 bucks at the toll or Erica for $20.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the review Mike! The Resort will continue to advocate for the improvement, maintenance and paving of the South Face Road as it is a good option for people travelling to the Resort.

name: Eric Halim
review_text: Please upgrade to chairlift. Walking to lift is too far to walk.

name: Muhammad Altaf
review_text: Very nice place for a day trip. Good activities and decent variety of snow gear and equipment hire

name: Jun Yu
review_text: So disappointed. It's poorly managed. It appears that they have oversold the tickets and we have been waiting for over an hour to get a parking spot. The little one will have no time to play before we have to get home. Strongly recommended against coming to Mt Baw Baw.

name: Jeff Lieu
review_text: Definitely a good snow experience for the family. Its awesome because not too crowded. Things are operated smoothly. Shuttlebus is a good option to avoid all the driving hassle upthere. Park at the entry, change to winter gear in dry weather, hop on the bus, and enjoy the snow!

name: Jessics Ku
review_text:
Hi there we had fun yesterday there with full snow. Excellent weather spent there. If I can suggest something that will be fitting ski or snowboard shoes specifically to kids or beginners please ensure the right sizes been given as my both kids weren't conformable and has to exit the class earlier. For example fit the shoes and ensure the ski pants are at the right position as inner layer was stuck in the boots which caused the pain. Kids are the main reason family go there. I would love to have this been taken care of.
Additionally, instructors can work in pair to the classes that would be needed specifically for the beginners group. Otherwise it's very well organised in facilities.

name: Adele Soni
review_text:
It was exciting until we got here, here is a rundown of the cost we paid out on the first hour for 2 kids and 3 adults --

Entry x $ 69
Coat hire, toboggan and boot hire x $ 198 ( we were happy to hire the snow gear )
Toboggan session to actually use the toboggan x $40 ( $20 per person )
5 hot drinks x $30
Food x $22.50

So basically don't hire the toboggan unless you're going to pay to use them, we used them for 30 minutes. Like honestly, if we had of known we wouldn't have hired it. To be honest, you're best going to Mount Hotham or Buller to be honest. Mount Baw Baw is a stop by. Not only that too much snow to use the ski slopes

name: Diana Rainbow
review_text: Epic! The snowgums colours were absolutely amazing as there had just been short shower of rain & the mist was also wafting through...the cafe was open & that was a real bonus!!!

name: Stanley Ye
review_text:
Mt Baw Baw is a great visit for those who want to go to the snow.
Entry is $67 per car.
Plenty of snow, went the last weekend of June.
Plenty of activities to do.
Less than 3 hours away from Melbourne.

name: Koonthos Koonthus
review_text:
This image captures a serene winter landscape, likely in a mountainous or high-altitude region. The foreground is dominated by a blanket of pristine white snow, with delicate blades of grass poking through, each one encrusted with sparkling frost, creating a beautiful, intricate texture. The low angle of the shot emphasizes the close-up detail of these icy formations.

In the midground and background, the sun is either rising or setting, casting a warm, golden glow across the horizon and filtering through the sparse trees, which appear to be covered in snow or frost themselves. The sky transitions from a soft blue directly overhead to hues of orange and yellow near the sun, with wispy clouds adding to the ethereal atmosphere. The overall impression is one of crisp, cold beauty, tranquility, and the quiet magic of a snowy morning or evening.

name: Sanjay Fernando
review_text:
Amazing experience. Definitely one of the best places to experience snow.

You will need snow chains for your car if you aren't driving a four wheel drive vehicle. Chains can be hired on the way (for a deposit) and fitted at the resort entrance for a $20 fee. There was a queue to get them installed. (Took about an hour for us)

There are plenty of activities such as skiing at the resort.

name: Heather King
review_text: No where to get coffees or meals, even on weekends this summer, a disgrace.

name: Paige
review_text: Wouldn't bother if it's not winter and if there is no snow. Waste of a drive and walks are very bland, not much to see. Dingos are not there in months that are not winter and everything is closed

name: Ian Fellowes
review_text: Loved it. Great weekend of good people and raking in the natural beauty

name: Luc Moore
review_text: It would be great to get a coffee or bit to eat mid week over the summer.  There was a partially stocked vending machine.  Interesting that you could get cup noodles and no boiling water.

name: Chris Melin
review_text: Lucky the vending machine is working and you can pay via tap. If you are a cyclist looking for food and drink at the top, it is thin pickings in October. At other times of the year I imagine it's very different.

name: aziar butler
review_text: A great experience to visit the snow. Mt baw baw has choices to toboggan or ski or snowboard. A bit expensive but worth it for the whole family.

name: Chris S
review_text:
A beautiful family-focused mountain, with facilities for day visitors (warm eating room, change room & public toilets, restaurant  and Cafe, First Aid)... Clothing and Equipment hire (including toboggans)  available..
2-2:30 hours from  Melbourne- Tyre Snow chains must be carried and used when instructed during winter months (can be pre-arranged and hired from Noojee/Icy Creek/Tanjil Bren)
As is lower altitude mountain compared to others in Vic, weather /snow conditions can be variable - plan accordingly and continue to respect the cold weather impact to health.

name: Good Coffee
review_text:
DO NOT GO.  $20 for tobogganing pass... for 1.5hrs!!!!   and it doesn't include rental.  half day (2 sessions) inc. hire close to $200 for 3 kids.  unbelievable!   it's August, it's 10 degrees, there is hardly any snow in the toboggan park.  Shame on you for charging so much for kids activity.

Also $64 for mountain entry then only 500m of road to the carpark!  outrageous. Same cost as Mt Buller and Hotham but the road there is much longer and resorts much higher and they provide something for the money at least ie. shuttle buses etc.   Baw Baw just provides you with kick to the wallet.

name: Asanka M
review_text: We wer there with kids and this was the first time. Was a great fun with kids. Very nice atmosphere, not too crowded like Mount Buller. Lot of waking trails filled with snow, where you could go and have fun. Rent toboggans else where much cheaper.

name: Al Abadi
review_text: I went to Mount Baw Baw to practice my snowboarding and it was horrible because I could not get a lift to the top, since they did not have a proper ski lift. I don't understand why they would not have this basic facility at a snow resort. I wasted a whole day and a good amount of money for nothing. I had to walk as far as I could to the top and then just get a slide down. I'm really disappointed. I do not recommend Mount Baw Baw at all.

name: Sadek Ali
review_text:
2 and half hours from the city towards the south east of Victoria, my Baw Baw is the nearest snow resort for for Victorian
Not a the biggest in Victoria but it has what you need for a snow day
It could get really busy during holiday and weekend, so make sure you book online for a quick entry at gate also rent a car chain before you get there otherwise you will be scammed by $49 even if it's sunny
There's different section for board and skiing and small section for Toboggan, which a $20 entry
Plenty parking sports, but make sure you don't park on the icy ground if you don't have a four wheel drive.

Nearby touristic suburbs like icy creek and noojee if you wanna have a night in a village, and save your self a 3 hours drive if you coming from the  side of town

name: Dinesh Prajapati
review_text:
We went there 4 families with kids on 31st Aug 2024 and it turn out to be disaster, first thing we bought 11 toboggans area tickets it was for 1:45 hours $20 each, but the area was filled with 1.5 feet of soft snow and they did not even try to compact it or not even mention when we bought tickets. I went back and complained and they told us you can complaint but no help whatsoever. I registered the complaint it's almost 8 days no reply or call at all.
On the way back coming down we had accident one of our family car lost traction and lost control and due to loose snow which they fitted there snap the brake line and lost brakes, luckily family was ok but one of their staff who scraps snow on the road with truck ask us to move car  even there was no brakes on car and car lost control again and hit other side of the curb towards hill side, luckily car stopped due to snow on side otherwise I would end up in the down hill with car.
The management is really bad and don't expect any help if anything happens there.
I would never go there or tell anyone to go there now onwards.

name: dji zzah
review_text: Beautiful part of the world

name: Tony King
review_text: Took my sons - one came over from WA and have never seen snow. Was awesome. Sally there is no ability to get up to the top of Mt Baw Baw unless you ski and I am a bit old for that and walking - would be nice to have a lift for non-ski ppl

name: Jesvin Jessy
review_text: Loved every moment at Mt Baw Baw

name: Mathew T
review_text: One of the best places I wish to go whenever possible.

name: SUNITA SOOD
review_text: Great

name: m shenoy
review_text: Resort is decent and there was excellent snow on Sat July 20.. but management is pathetic..had to wait 3 hours for snow chain fitting..3 hours absolutely inside the car was an ordeal we will never forget( we were just 500 metres away from the snow chain fitting place at Baw Baw and it was around 1030am) .Could only reach the resort at around 3 pm.I even paid  entry day fees of 64$ online but what's the use

name: Subhashi Jayasekara
review_text: So relaxing

name: Eric Lau
review_text: Drive straight to the resort and very convenient.

name: Hazel
review_text:
Expensive!
Have to pay $64 to enter the snow area. Beside that they charge $49 for snow chain for a small portion of road on top, when there is no snow on the road anyway because it's cleaned with trucks and they know you will not use it. Carpark worker was rude and ignorant. If you don't like working in cold go work somewhere else!

name: Walter A. P. A.
review_text: watch the video, approximate cost with car, skis, clothes, food 250 dollars to 300 dollars per person.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the review and video! :)

name: Milind Prajapati
review_text: The customer service was great. We had ski lessons with this instructor, Henry, and he was amazing. He taught us really well. He totally deserves an A+. But it was a bit expensive, so I have to take one star off.
response_from_owner_text:
Thank you for your feedback and glad to hear you had a great time. We always aim to keep costs as low as possible, especially for lessons. 

Snow is unfortunately an expensive business but lessons here are a great way to get into things without the high costs of other Resorts where day lift passes for example can be over $200.

name: Matt O'Meara
review_text: Disgusting attitude from your staff this past weekend when I was part of a group visiting the mountain. If you can't speak to and treat your customers in a better manner, perhaps you should seek another job where you are not dealing with the general public.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Matt,
We are sorry to hear about your experience. If you can please submit your feedback with more details via our feedback form on the website we can follow this up for you.

name: Amelie Llorca
review_text:
I don't know why you have to pay $64 to get up the mountain! in Europe access to the mountains is free, rethink that and you might have more visitors!!!
we were lucky we had snow. Add $20 per person to access the toboggan run and $20 to rent a toboggan for 1.45 hours.
One run open out of two and magic carpet not working! A total rip off! If you are in the area and you want to see snow but do not ski try Mount St Gwinear it's free.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Amelie,
We are sorry to hear about your experience.
Resort access fees are charged across all Resorts in Victoria and cover the cost of road clearing, maintenance and other things. The fees are set by Alpine Resorts Victoria and are unlikely to be removed as that is just how resorts are set up in Victoria.

We love St. Gwinear but would like to note that it has snow for tobogganing a small part of the season, our toboggan park has been open all season, there are also no downhill skiing and minimal facilities. 

We do try to keep our costs as low as possible for families but appreciate and take on board feedback where we can. 

We hope to see you again here or on the other side of the hill at St Gwinear.

name: Wendy Peterman
review_text: Was great family day out! Expensive? Yes! Shame the magic carpet for kids wasn't working, and we still had to pay $20 per head to use the tabaggon run. Couldn't understand why.. overall, the whole family loved it, but make sure to have alot of funds in the account

name: Raccy Beats
review_text: had an awesome time and pete at the ski hire was an absolute delight. however when returning snow pants i had accidentally left my phone in pocket and before i realised it was too late and they went into the wash so my phone is now broken unable to fix it, it is my fault but maybe in future before washing rental clothes please check the pockets for belongings for other people so this doesnt happen again.

name: Berin Couacaud
review_text: Very educational

name: Angie Putri
review_text: Too pretty, easy hike and wonderful weather
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Angita!
Thank you for your review and we hope you enjoyed the fantastic weather.

name: Alex Pape
review_text: Big hill

name: Logan
review_text: Good views and all round a nice place to visit in both summer and winter.

name: Mark L
review_text: I enjoyed riding my motorbike to this village. Unfortunately, it was summer and the 1 cafe was not open. The place was void of activity but it is worth a visit
response_from_owner_text: Hi Mark, we're glad you enjoyed your trip. Recently the cafe typically opens Thursday to Monday during green season so we're sorry you missed it this time.

name: David Holgye
review_text: Good coffee and I had a great lunch

name: Dean Fitzpatrick
review_text: Would be good to see in the snow!

name: Raff Dwyer
review_text: not much snow during most times

name: Russell Stapleton
review_text: So much snow this weekend thanks to a huge fall on Friday. No crowds and lots of fun for kids and adults. No lifts running or ski hire on the mountain. But there's still hot food and drinks at the village.

name: Tony Edge
review_text: Fantastic experience loved it, if timed right it's a great place for the family to spend hours doing activities or a casual stole around.

name: Dineshika Nawarathna
review_text:
Got there a bit late (September first week) so no snow except some artificial stuff that covers max 2 sizes of football pitches area. But, good enough for kids to have fun, although not for adults. Totally agree with the entrance fee for park maintenance and essential services.

But it was super sunny, still had to pay for chains just to put them inside the boot during the entire day. It is okay for safety, but it would be super practical if they provide hire service at the entrance down there on snow days or possible weathers and also village park on sunny days in case of weather changes without making it compulsory to rent it at the entrance gate everyday. So people do not feel bad or unnecessary fees to enjoy the park.

We wanted to hit the highway asap and choose  the other side/ South Face Road and enjoy that part of the road as well. That was the worst idea of the trip, as the entire road is really not suitable for even AWD with all weather tyres as the whole road is filled with mortars and not carpeted/ sealed upto Thomson Valley Rd all the way. Honestly, not worthy to check the whole other side whatever it shows on the map. Go back through the Baw Baw Tourist Rd even though it is longer.

Cheers...

name: Fernando Ghelfi
review_text: Great experience as an introduction to ski resorts with small kids.

name: James Baker
review_text:
I love this place - an excellent get away.. Gets busy and exciting.. And offers lovely outdoor experiences - recent trip was with limited snow but this offered excellent bushwalks on tracks that I as child wld ski by cross country skiing

One or 2 runs were avtive while I was there and downhill skiiers and snowbowrders were enjoying it, also the tobogoning run was getting regular use - lots of fun

When you're out in snow use common sense, good planning and look after yourself and others in your group.

The accommodation we stayed at was superb

name: Andy Michelis
review_text: Fantastic day out and well worth the drive from Melbourne. Very easy access to parking and toboggan area for the kids :-).  Cross country skiing and downhill are available.  There are two main eating shops and bbq and warm eating area.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Andy, thank you for your kind review and we hope to see you again this winter.

name: Nikul Patel
review_text: Really disappointed, no real weather condition mentioned in the website, there was no snow at all and you must need chain... just pay for everything but no service at all

name: JAMES O'NEAL
review_text: Ripped off $62 for entry per car. Had to pay $39 for chains and there was no snow or ice on the road

name: Arnab Mondal
review_text: Good Place for family

name: R T
review_text:
Very difficult drive up the mountain. Roads need to be improved considering the amount of money and revenue that this place generates and Parks Victoria does not seem to want to spend the time nor money to improve the roads.
Works should be carried out in off season.?????

Little bit disappointing, snow was very minimal.

name: Hannah Veltri
review_text: Website said it had snowed 20cm but hadn't actually snowed just the fake stuff, you also have to pay for EVERYTHING, they don't even check that you have tickets for the lifts so it doesn't even matter in the end. After being there for a few hours all there fake snow had disappeared and they weren't adding more so it made snow boarding kinda painful if you fall over a lot, all the other years I've been here it's been wonderful and it is out of peak atm but they could charge less for some things and let you know in the website weather it's actual snow of just fake stuff

name: BuckleyTilers
review_text: So disappointed with a trip to Baw Baw. Althought I can sympathise with their lack of control on the snow coverage, the $89 lift pass when there was only  1 T Bar open and so little snow that my family walked up to the top of the 100m snow run is appalling. The booking system is confusing also. I assumed due to having to book a day that my ticket would be void if I did not go, regardless of the snow cover, so we went anyway. I however think a discounted ski pass or free ski pass when you have paid the $55 just to enter the resort would be justified if in fact the lift wasn't even needed. I hate to think the amount of revenue you raised out of today, as there was only 20 passes left for the day. Very upsetting and dissapointing, and simply dangerous to have that many people on one 100m run.

name: Hien Dang
review_text: Our family was at Mt BawBaw yesterday. What a terrible trip after years of not visiting. I can't believe everything is so bad now, from high entrance fee, weak management, poor service. It took me almost 3 hours to get there and my kids only had 1 hour for playing toboggan and then had to come back because it was late. Dont go to Mt Bawbaw, it just ruins your day. Never comeback

name: Sukun Pandya
review_text: One of nicest Alpine areas in south East of Melbourne

name: Tran Oanh
review_text: We had extremely bad experience with Mt Baw Baw services. Really poor management during this peak season. We had to wait for 3 hours just to get the ticket and the wheel chains to be able to go to the mountain. Although we drove the 4WD, we still had to wait for more than 1 hour just to get the wheel chains to carry it in the car. We asked if we can get it and and go without going the the fitting line but they refused as others already waited. They should have priority line for those only need to carry the chains without fitting to drive through. I felt so bad for the staff working at the fitting station as they were only 2 but have to fit hundreds of cars all day. They looked extremely tired. Needless to say, the pass is $62/day for nothing, we still need to pay extra for the services such as toboggan. We hired the toboggan but playing outside of the toboggan park because it was too crowded in there and I felt it wasn't safe for young kids. Then they came and said we were not allow to play there without any signs saying so just because we didn't pay for the toboggan park tickets. The toilets were over crowded and super dirty. The hot tap water in the abundant toilet was broken, my two year old and I had to wash hands with cold water only in the middle of the snow rain outside. What an experience! We wouldn't recommend Mt Baw Baw and wouldn't come back next year!

name: Quoc Cong Tran
review_text:
Terrible Management, hundreds of cars waiting for taking snow chains or fitting chains...Only 2 workers...Most of customers waiting 2-3 hours waiting in car with the kids screaming.
This is the first time I came back here after covid period, They charged everything, everything is expensive with a terrible service....toilets are super dirty and smelly...They charged everything and give you the worse service....We wont come back ever again...and dont bother to go to mt baw baw...it would give you stress and tireness only.

After reply from the resort: They still dont see the poor traffic management and sevices.
We were advised we didnt need to fit the snow chains as our group have 4 4x4 drive cars. Why would you keep all of 4x4 waiting in the fitting bays instead of just giving them chain and keep going? so it would fasten the waiting line.  Plus poor signages....thats why were hundred of cars waiting for the non sense stuff.
response_from_owner_text:
I do apologise for the wait yesterday but unfortunately when it is snowing we prioritise safety which means fitting chains to cars for those people unable to fit their own. We had 6 people fitting chains in the bottom chain bay and 2 at chain bay 3. We were also running shuttles which we were encouraging people to take. It is much quieter midweek or outside school holidays. Unfortunately you picked the busiest and snowiest day to come up.
We did have a number of cars who didn't fit chains despite being advised they had to which resulted in them sliding off the road and holding up traffic even more. Luckily there were no injuries

name: Dolly Thornton
review_text: Not much snow, entry fee and Tobogan service fee charge ($63 and $12 ), felt Ripped off. View was beautiful. Don't follow road sign saying 80 , just do 30 to 35, if anyone want to return home safely.

Fun experience but very expensive.
Cafe had nice chips but again crazy pricing!
Wish there was a bit more space that you could sit around and build snowmen or have snowball fights, very crowded small space.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Hailey,
Thank you for your feedback - we have made note of your comments regarding the space for the consideration of management.

In regards to price - we do think that our prices remain affordable in what is an expensive industry globally. Lift passes, lessons (and event chicken parmas) for example are great value when comparing to competitors. We have implemented discounts on items such as Resort Entry this season in order to keep things as affordable as possible. We will take your feedback onboard when pricing for 2023 and hope we can see you again.

name: Dave Wade
review_text:
Look it's not Mt Buller or Mt Hotham but it's not trying to be either. Good fun little mountain that the whole family can enjoy. Kids learning to ride is the main target market here but parents can have some fun as well.
Staff were exceptional!!!
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Dave,
Thank you so much for the review. We work hard to provide a fun, safe family friendly destination and gateway into the snow for people up here so this is great to hear.

name: Leebsterftw
review_text:
It's a nice area, has Alpine dingo enclosure.
Bit pricey.
response_from_owner_text:
Hello leebster,
Thank you for the shout out to adorable dingoes. If you have specific products you with to provide feedback on in regards to price so we can review them please send a submission using the form on our website or update this review. We hope to see you back again green season or winter!

name: Corey O'Leary
review_text:
This resort has gone downhill big time over the years. A group of us buy a season pass every year, but this year we have barely gone up cause half the mountain has been closed most of the season. And now we are into spring they are only opening 1 run yet they have coverage over all the runs?

I don't understand what their business strategy is, but keeping 80% of the runs closed for a majority of the season isn't going to entice people to visit & spend money.

Unfortunately come next season, will be the first year in a long time we won't be taking up a season pass. It's just not worth your money to be able to use it so little.

We normally make 10-15 trips up per season, this year we have made 5. Would have been cheaper for us to just buy day passes each time.

Such a shame cause while this resort is small in comparison to the other big mountains, Baw Baws runs have personality & while short, lots of fun. (When more than 1 run is open)
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Corey,
We're sorry to hear about your experience this season. As you may be aware; the tourism industry has faced significant challenges as a result of staff shortages - this certainly has impacted us being a smaller Resort - rest assured we will always open as many lifts as we can and the conditions allow.

As a season pass holder we have asked a manager to follow up by email with you to help resolve this - so we can have you back again next season hopefully.

name: Faiz Khan
response_from_owner_text: Thankyou for the review and sharing your photos Faiz! :)

name: Khushi Ram Dangi
review_text: Good place

name: Leo V
review_text: Seems be better this year, probably because of the heavy snow. Does get packed. Food options are simple and gets packed during peak hour, kinda pricey and fairly average but to be expected. Get in early to avoid 2wd cars with chains. No issues climbing up the hill with the 80 series. Worth a visit.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Leo, thank you for your feedback which we will pass on to the team. We do our best to keep prices affordable in what is an expensive industry and hope we can see you again next season.

name: Ben Ong
review_text: It was a disappointing experience as there was some confusion with the toboggan run. We bought magic carpet lift for the family only to find the Frosti Frog run was closed. Contacted the management and were told it was opened but on the other side. We missed the fine print when purchasing the pass thinking the barcode was the ticket, which we should have gone to the office to exchange for tag. Even so, the distance to the opened toboggan run was actually 3x walking distance of Frosti Frog. Carrying 5 toboggan with impatient kids doesn't help. Suggested to them to make a sign for the opened toboggan run instead.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Ben,
We're sorry to hear about your experience due to the temporarily relocated toboggan park. Please send us an email at Guest Services and we will have a manager get in touch to find a solution for you and your family so you can visit us again in the future.

name: Thouseef KM
review_text: One of the nearest snow mountains from Melbourne city, which is around 3 hours drive. When we reached there, we got some fresh snows from morning but not snowing then. Good place to spend a day doing skiing , tobogganing and enjoying snows. This place is relatively small compare to Buller. But if you are visiting during the peak winter, it is recommended that you wear some warm clothes, snow boots and hand gloves. You can hire them from here as well, there are enough if them here. Normal shoes are slippery to walk in the snow. There are good restaurants, you can sit there and warm your selves having some pizza, coffee etc. If you are driving to the mountain, make sure you carry the snow chains for your vehicle, you can hire them at the gate. It is mandatory to carry one during winter, but needs to wear it only if it snows and roads are slippery. Only last few kilometres, may be around 3 to 4km has risk of snows, but mostly they clear the snow from the road. There is enough car parking at the mountain top, but if it is filled, you have to park it at the gate and take the shuttle bus service.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the detailed review and we hope to see you again.

Cafe restaurant up there serves good food, coffee was so ok... good spot for toboggan & , however not a huge area as mount Hotham.

review_text: A lot of fun and a lot of space to enjoy the snow the only issues is none of the places said that they have atms or that they can withdraw cash so take it with you!

review_text: I pre booked for the Queen's birthday Sunday but when we got to the resort around 2pm we had to wait in the car another hour to find out that there was no room. Will go to lake mountain next time as they limit the number of people before you travel.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Mark,
We're sorry to hear about your troubles. Unfortunately on Sunday we received an unprecedented amount of arrivals (many hundreds of vehicles) who hadn't pre-booked, and some people such as yourself who had planned ahead were impacted.
Please feel free to send us an email and we can try to find a solution to get you back again at a less busy time, otherwise, Lake Mountain is a great place and we wish you the best there!

Thanks for your review! The Resort has sold out on most weekends - we can recommend booking early before the season, midweek or in September where we have availability left - or staying in a local town like Tanjil Bren, Noojee, Willow Grove, Erica, Walhalla which are all very beautiful and 20 minutes to 1 hour away.

response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the review Bashir, and that is great advice! See you again.

review_text: I lv ridding the bike up here motorcycle that is. There's a nice restaurant to have a  coffee  or a nice meal the views are good but they need to trim back the trees at the restaurant they spiol the view. It takes around 2 hours from eastern suburbs to get up there but it's thick bush fantastic views from Noojee on wards and don't forget to check out the Toorongo  Falls  just out of Noojee
response_from_owner_text:
Thanks Henry,
We will pass your feedback about the trees on to our operations team. Permits for vegetation removal in alpine areas can be tough but we'll see what we can do as we also love the ocean views!

name: Jim Casson
review_text: Great place and food and start thanks
response_from_owner_text: We'll pass this on to the Restaurant team! Please come again :)

name: Tom Durrand
review_text: For cyclists this this is more than a mountain, it's a savage monster. This is by far the toughest hill in Australia, and I wouldn't be exaggerating to much to say in the entire world! No reprieve from constant gradients of above the double digits for more than 5 kilometres! But don't get me wrong this is also one of my favourites. When you step of the bike at the top, panting like a dog on a 40 degree day, take in the the beautiful scenery and sit down at the amazing cafe, it all becomes worth it. I dare you to take the plunge in to the hardest climb Down Under.
response_from_owner_text: So much respect for making it to the top, Tom! We hope to see more cyclists conquering the mountain in Green Season 2022-23!

name: Jeff DeMaria
review_text:
This whole mountain is so very poorly managed, which is a shame. Would never recommend for skiing/boarding - even for learners the stupid outdated lift systems are super challenging and do nothing to help people actually learn snowsports.

EDIT 30/1/22: The response form management, 3 years later shows how little they actually care about customer feedback. And no, T-Bars and Poma are not widely used around the world...at least not at real resorts that have invested in new infrastructure at some point over the last 50 years. There's not even a single actual chair lift at this pimple of a mountain. If you want to learn head to Buller where they have actual lifts and beginner hills steep enough to actually gain some momentum.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Jeff,
We're sorry to hear about your experience. We strongly disagree with the opinion that the Resort is not ideal for beginners and intermediates. In fact, we believe it is the complete opposite.

We do understand that Poma and T-Bar lifts are more challenging to learn at first however knowing how to use them is an important skill for any skiier or boarder as these types of tow lifts are common across the world.

Mt Baw Baw offers a relaxed environment in which those who are new or returning to skiing can learn to ski/board and ride tow lifts and we hope you can give us another chance in the future.

name: Tharindu Dhanushka
review_text: One of the best snow destination
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Tharindu,
Thank you for taking the time to give us feedback! We hope to see you again.

name: Lis Conde
review_text: We went there during the summer, but it was raining. The mountain itself is amazing, really thick bushy forest. Was happy to see nature this way. We saw wallabies, geese, tons of rosellas. During the winter, the resort seems to be a money making machine. You have to pay like 30 dollars a car just to enter the mountain. Although they do have a dingoes in captivity and there were a really interesting sight. Bet it is fun to ski here but pricey.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Lis,
Thank you for your detailed review. Mt Baw Baw is definitely a beautiful place!

The Resort Entry fee in winter helps cover the costs of road maintenance, snow clearing, traffic management and customer safety which are expensive to operate.

You can reduce costs and environmental impact by travelling in the same car with a group of friends or family.

Once again thank you for the review and we hope you can visit again soon.

name: Adam Selent
review_text: Great place to visit in summer, hiking, mountain biking, trampolines or just checking out the wildflowers. Winter time it's a great mountain for beginners
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Adam,
Thanks so much for the review. Green season is certainly an amazing time to visit the Victorian Alps and we hope to see you again.

name: Syed Arshaq Hassan

Hi Syed,
Thank you for the review! We're always 10 degrees cooler up here so a great option for summer.

Hi Iryna,
We're sorry to hear about your experience. In 2021 season due to COVID impacts on lift capacity we charged a flat fee for lift tickets on weekends. Flexi-date pricing is likely to return when COVID lift capacity limits are no longer in place.

We hope you can give us another chance in the future.

name: Cheryl Scott
review_text:
Sadly not much snow but still a pretty place to visit
Lovely lunch overlooking beautiful outlook
Coming back for the Frisbee golf???
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking the time for a review Cheryl. We hope we can see you again when snow conditions are better or during green season for hiking and disc golf!

name: CHERYL SCOTT

The remaining terrain relies on natural snow conditions which do vary season-to-season.We recommend checking the live cameras and lift report in the future and visiting when conditions are suitable to your needs.
Once again, we apologies we couldn't provide a better experience and hope you can give us a chance in the future.

name: Caelan Gration
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the review Caelan. If you have specific feedback on how we can improve from a 3 to 5 please send us a message on our contact form. We hope to see you again.

name: shaohui Fu
review_text: Called 5 times no answer on phone need more staff.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Shaohui,
We're sorry to hear about your experience.

Due to COVID lockdowns in 2020 and 2021 we received extremely high volumes of calls during certain times. Our team members were working as hard as they could to get back to people as fast as possible and process refund requests or date changes.

In general we recommend guests unable to get through on phone lines send an email rather than making multiple calls as this helps speed up our response time.

We hope we can see you again in the future.

name: Kat Curie
review_text: Beware, school holidays - super busy for a little snow...Must Prebook though - especially, if you need toboggans. The traffic horrendous, took us greater than 1hr to queue before getting into resort.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi KitKat,
We're sorry to hear about your experience. When COVID capacity limits are in place as well as increased checking requirements we strongly recommend booking online in advance to reduce delays and avoid missing out. Hopefully in the future these challenges won't be such a problem and delays and sell outs can be avoided.

School holidays like many places is often our busiest time of year. You can avoid peak crowds by looking at off peak times, or visiting during the weekdays. Early September for example is a great time and snow conditions can be really good then.

We hope you can give us another chance in the future.

response_from_owner_text:

We're very sorry to hear about your experience waiting for food. We will pass this on to management here. There are typically multiple food and beverage venues operating on the mountain during snow season and we will follow up with why this wasn't the case during your stay.

We hope we can see you again in the future.

review_text: Entrance fee is too high and forced to have snow chains even there's no snow on the day or or snow on the road. Might be good for sky but not a great place for a tobogans.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Tharindu,
Thank you for your review. We require guests to carry chains for customer safety reasons. While it may be sunny in the morning conditions can change quickly and those stuck at the top of the mountain without chains can get stuck. Mt Baw Baw's resort entry road has some of the steepest sections in Australia and safety of our customers is our first priority.

We hope you can visit us again in the future. If visiting Victoria's resorts regularly we recommend purchasing a set of chains.

In terms of the Resort Entry fee Mt Baw Baw remains a highly affordable option compared to competitors. Google "How Much Mt Baw Baw" for a price overview and comparison.

name: Bat Robertson
review_text:
As the closest ski field to Melbourne, Mt. Baw Baw is best avoided on the weekends if you dont want to poleaxed by someone who doesn't know how to ski or thinks its appropriate to haul their 80kg adult carcass down a tobogan slope like a giggling idiot, ploughing into half a dozen kids.   Having to pay to use the tobogan conveyer just to escort a 5yo to the top of the run and safely send him down his own is a epic rip off.

If management does read this, perhaps actually given visitors an option of a footpath they can go up and down for free might be a option, as is designating a under 10s/family play area for toboganning/snow play to the kids don't get pummeled by adults might make the resort even more family friendly.  General lack of signage about, so had to walk about the place to find things that should be easy to find ( like lift passes)

Lastly, ( and this is very serious) the lack of designated, separate footpaths from the lower car parks to the entrance needs to addressed as forces visitors to share the road with vehicles in wet, slippery and low light conditions. This is an OH&S issue.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Bat,
Thanks for your detailed feedback. We will take this on board and pass it on to management particularly the feedback about road access. This is something we are aware of and seeking to address.

In terms of the toboggan park; the magic carpet lift operates to improve safety on the park as it prevents people walking back up the toboggan slope. It also improves the experience as walking up hill repeatedly is not necessary.  The fee to use the lift covers to cost of staffing, power, maintenance and operation of the lift for the safety and improved experience of Guests. All users need to be ticketed for liability reasons.

There is space for snow play all around the village subject to conditions and we do endeavor to provide a snow play area in times of poor conditions, but we will take this feedback on board.

We hope that you can give us another chance in the future and look forward to seeing you and your family again.

review_translated_text: Check the weather before coming here. If there is no snow, you will be very depressed. Then... the road here is really bad, the mountain road has 18 bends. My personal suggestion is, if there is no room on the mountain, don't stay overnight, just go home after a day of fun.

response_from_owner_text:
Hi Hana,
Thank you for your feedback.
Both Mt Baw Baw and Lake Mountain require chains to be carried regardless of snow conditions when visiting. Often it will snow midway through the day or stay and then it becomes impossible to get back down so this is for safety reasons. Driving down is often more risky than coming up.

We're sorry to hear about your experience at the toboggan park. Since this review improvements have been made to snowmaking to ensure the toboggan park can better handle peak visitation. In any case we recommend day trippers check the live cameras before visiting to check conditions as they vary through the season.

The Resort entry fee covers snow clearing, traffic management, road maintenance and staffing costs which are expensive. We recommend carpooling for those who wish to share the cost of entry as well as reduce environmental impact.
We hope to see you again in the future.

review_text: Great day trip, just over an hours drive from Traralgon. Food was decent, all meals were around 15$ with chips, rental gear was around 60$ for the day but goes half price from 1pm. Definitely more for beginners/ family but a great little day trip for my friend who had never seen the snow.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Connor,
Thank you for the informative review. We hope to see you again in future seasons! We definitely agree that customers consider all chain hire options before departing as there can be delays if visiting a Victorian snow resort without pre-hiring or booking. We always hope people's journey here can be as smooth as possible and chain hire and fitting can be a challenge.

They promote shuttle bus & charge $25 per person if you have to leave the vehicle because you don't have the snow chain.

I refused to take the shuttle bus and decided to wait there until someone returns a snow chain as it was a afternoon and people have started drive back home.

As soon as they notice I'm not going to take the shuttle bus, a bloke who work there showed up with a chain which they "didn't have" earlier. I didn't see a returning  vehicle which has my tyre size... May be someone "secretly" returned a chain to them... LOL

response_from_owner_text:
Hi Daniel,
We're sorry to hear about your experience during the 2018 season.

The Resort has the responsibility to open and close the road during heavy snowfall for the safety of Guests both entering and exiting the Resort. There are times where the road is closed due to car accidents or heavy snow. Rest assured we do not stop people from leaving for any other reasons for their own safety.

We hope you can give us another chance in the future and if you have time would appreciate your feedback on your experience through the form on the website so we can ensure positive guest interactions in the future.
